msgctxt "sn12.46:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.46:0.2"
msgid "5. Gahapativagga "
msgstr "5. Householders "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 46. Aññatarabrāhmaṇasutta → aññataraṃ (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.46:0.3"
msgid "46. Aññatarabrāhmaṇasutta "
msgstr "46. A Certain Brahmin "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn12.46:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.46:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then a certain brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "sn12.46:1.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn12.46:2.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, so karoti so paṭisaṃvedayatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, does the person who does the deed experience the result?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.46:2.2"
msgid "“‘So karoti so paṭisaṃvedayatī’ti kho, brāhmaṇa, ayameko anto”. "
msgstr "“‘The person who does the deed experiences the result’: this is one extreme, brahmin.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.76, sc3
msgctxt "sn12.46:3.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, añño karoti, añño paṭisaṃvedayatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Then does one person do the deed and another experience the result?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.46:3.2"
msgid "“‘Añño karoti, añño paṭisaṃvedayatī’ti kho, brāhmaṇa, ayaṃ dutiyo anto. "
msgstr "“‘One person does the deed and another experiences the result’: this is the second extreme. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.46:3.3"
msgid "Ete te, brāhmaṇa, ubho ante anupagamma majjhena tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti: "
msgstr "Avoiding these two extremes, the Realized One teaches by the middle way: "

msgctxt "sn12.46:3.4"
msgid "‘avijjāpaccayā saṅkhārā; "
msgstr "‘Ignorance is a condition for choices. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.46:3.5"
msgid "saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "Choices are a condition for consciousness. … "

msgctxt "sn12.46:3.6"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "

msgctxt "sn12.46:3.7"
msgid "Avijjāya tveva asesavirāganirodhā saṅkhāranirodho; "
msgstr "When ignorance fades away and ceases with nothing left over, choices cease. "

msgctxt "sn12.46:3.8"
msgid "saṅkhāranirodhā … pe … "
msgstr "When choices cease … "

msgctxt "sn12.46:3.9"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī’”ti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn12.46:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, so brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, the brahmin said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn12.46:4.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … "
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! … "

msgctxt "sn12.46:4.3"
msgid "upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.46:4.4"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

